            <summary>
                <![CDATA[
                    Features of Chesta Create chemical potential diagrams for multi-component systems 2D (with 2 axes) and 3D (with 3 axes) diagrams&hellip;
                ]]>
            </summary>
        <content type="html">
            <![CDATA[
                <h2><figure class="post__image"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://n-hatada.github.io/chesta/media/posts/1/ChestaScreenshot.png" sizes="(max-width: 48em) 100vw, 768px" srcset="https://n-hatada.github.io/chesta/media/posts/1/responsive/ChestaScreenshot-xs.png 300w ,https://n-hatada.github.io/chesta/media/posts/1/responsive/ChestaScreenshot-sm.png 480w ,https://n-hatada.github.io/chesta/media/posts/1/responsive/ChestaScreenshot-md.png 768w"  alt="" width="2071" height="1060"></figure></h2>
<h2>Features of Chesta</h2>
<h3>Create chemical potential diagrams for multi-component systems</h3>
<ul style="list-style-type: circle;">
<li>2D (with 2 axes) and <strong>3D (with 3 axes) diagrams</strong> can be created.</li>
<li>Chemical systems with more than 3 components can be handled. (Cutting and projection features are provided to reduce the dimension of the diagrams.)</li>
</ul>
<h3><span style="font-family: var(--editor-font-family); font-size: inherit;">Customize diagrams</span></h3>
<ul style="list-style-type: circle;">
<li>Several types of axes such as activity, energy, electrical potential, and temperature are available. This enables creation of <strong>Ellingham diagrams</strong> and <strong>Pourbaix (Potential-pH, E-pH) diagrams</strong>.</li>
<li><strong>Temperature and the activity of each phase can be changed</strong> and applied in the diagrams instantly.</li>
</ul>
<h3><span style="font-family: var(--editor-font-family); font-size: inherit;">Output images (in BMP, JPG, and EMF formats)</span></h3>
<ul style="list-style-type: circle;">
<li>Vector images (EMF) can be edited in other softwares without degradation.</li>
</ul>
<h3><span style="font-family: var(--editor-font-family); font-size: inherit;">Output coordinates of equilibrium points and activities of chemical species</span></h3>
<ul style="list-style-type: circle;">
<li>Chesta can be utilized as a tool for equilibrium calculations.</li>
</ul>
<h2>System requirements</h2>
<p>Microsoft Windows 7 or later (64 bit)</p>
<h2>Downloads</h2>
<h3>Chesta 3.4.1 (Latest version)</h3>
